Before entering this section, the main request goes through the GET method from `S3AclController`. It is the change of this method which allows to transform the request GET request (to retrieve ACLs S3) into request HEAD. The section you mentioned above allows us to have permissions to read S3 ACLs (like the GET method, which was used before).

In addition, in the logs provided in a previous comment, before the changes, we can see a GET request reaching the `container-server` (or` object-server`). To reproduce these logs, you can run these commands (don't forget to enable `s3_acl` in the` proxy-server` conf):
```
$ aws s3api get-bucket-acl --bucket mybucket
